s="breadcrumbs__item"><a aria-label="Home page" class="breadcrumbs__link" href="../../index.html"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="breadcrumbHomeIcon_YNFT"><path d="M10 19v-5h4v5c0 .55.45 1 1 1h3c.55 0 1-.45 1-1v-7h1.7c.46 0 .68-.57.33-.87L12.67 3.6c-.38-.34-.96-.34-1.34 0l-8.36 7.53c-.34.3-.13.87.33.87H5v7c0 .55.45 1 1 1h3c.55 0 1-.45 1-1z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg></a></li><li itemscope="" itemprop="itemListElement" itemtype="https://schema.org/ListItem" class="breadcrumbs__item"><a class="breadcrumbs__link" itemprop="item" href="../../category/swap-api"><span itemprop="name">Swap API</span></a><meta itemprop="position" content="1"></li><li class="breadcrumbs__item"><span class="breadcrumbs__link">Advanced Topics</span><meta itemprop="position" content="2"></li><li itemscope="" itemprop="itemListElement" itemtype="https://schema.org/ListItem" class="breadcrumbs__item breadcrumbs__item--active"><span class="breadcrumbs__link" itemprop="name">How to Set Your Token Allowances</span><meta itemprop="position" content="3"></li></ul></nav><div class="tocCollapsible_ETCw theme-doc-toc-mobile tocMobile_ITEo"><button type="button" class="clean-btn tocCollapsibleButton_TO0P">On this page</button></div><div class="theme-doc-markdown markdown"><h1>How to Set Your Token Allowances</h1><p>A <a href="https://tokenallowance.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">token allowances</a> is required if you want a third-party to move funds on your behalf. In short, you are allowing them to move your tokens.</p><p>In our case, we would like the 0x Exchange Proxy smart contract to trade our ERC20 tokens for us, so we need to write to the ERC20 contract of that token, and approve an allowance for 0x Exchange Proxy (i.e. allow it to move a certain amount of tokens on our behalf us).</p><p>To do so, we will need to give an allowance to the <code>allowanceTarget</code> parameter that&#x27;s returned by the <a href="https://0x.org/docs/0x-swap-api/advanced-topics/0x-swap-api/api-references/get-swap-v1-quote"><code>/quote</code></a> and <a href="https://0x.org/docs/0x-swap-api/advanced-topics/0x-swap-api/api-references/get-swap-v1-price"><code>/price</code></a> Swap API endpoints. The <code>allowanceTarget</code> is the the target contract address, in our case the 0x Exchange Proxy smart contract address on the relevant network (see full list of address <a href="../../introduction/0x-cheat-sheet#exchange-proxy-addresses">here</a>). Read more about <code>allowanceTarget</code> <a href="../api-references/get-swap-v1-quote">here</a>. Note that <code>allowanceTarget</code> is only relevant when selling an ERC20 token.</p><div class="theme-admonition theme-admonition-info alert alert--info admonition_LlT9"><div class="admonitionHeading_tbUL"><span class="admonitionIcon_kALy"><svg viewBox="0 0 14 16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M7 2.3c3.14 0 5.7 2.56 5.7 5.7s-2.56 5.7-5.7 5.7A5.71 5.71 0 0 1 1.3 8c0-3.14 2.56-5.7 5.7-5.7zM7 1C3.14 1 0 4.14 0 8s3.14 7 7 7 7-3.14 7-7-3.14-7-7-7zm1 3H6v5h2V4zm0 6H6v2h2v-2z"></path></svg></span>info</div><div class="admonitionContent_S0QG"><p>For swaps with &quot;ETH&quot; as sellToken, wrapping &quot;ETH&quot; to &quot;WETH&quot; or unwrapping &quot;WETH&quot; to &quot;ETH&quot; no allowance is needed, a null address of <code>0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000</code> is then returned instead.</p></div></div><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="setting-allowances-for-0x-api-quotes">Setting Allowances for 0x API quotes<a href="how-to-set-your-token-allowances#setting-allowances-for-0x-api-quotes" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Setting Allowances for 0x API quotes" title="Direct link to Setting Allowances for 0x API quotes">â€‹</a></h2><p>There are several ways to set a token allowance, both programmatically and through a UI. We will cover options for both methods below.</p><h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="using-wagmi">Using wagmi<a href="how-to-set-your-token-allowances#using-wagmi" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Using wagmi" title="Direct link to Using wagmi">â€‹</a></h3><p>wagmi has a number of hooks that can help us read and write to contracts.</p><ul><li>Call <a href="https://wagmi.sh/react/hooks/useContractRead" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><code>useContractRead</code></a> to check if the ERC20 token we are interested in has approved an allowance to 0x Exchange Proxy.</li><li>Call <a href="https://wagmi.sh/react/prepare-hooks/usePrepareContractWrite" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><code>usePrepareContractWrite</code></a> and <a href="https://wagmi.sh/react/hooks/useContractWrite" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><code>useContractWrite</code></a> to write the approval to the token contract.</li></ul><p>See the full code implementation <a href="https://github.com/0xProject/0x-nextjs-demo-app/blob/main/pages/Price/index.tsx" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a> from our <a href="https://github.com/0xProject/0x-nextjs-demo-app/tree/main" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Next.js 0x demo app</a>.</p><div class="language-javascript codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_biex"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-javascript codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token comment" style="color:#999988;font-style:italic">// fetch quote</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain"></span><span class="token spread operator" style="color:#393A34">...</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain"></span><span cla